com.team1829.library

Class CarbonUI.UIConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.team1829.library.CarbonUI.UIConfig
  • Enclosing class:
    CarbonUI

    public class CarbonUI.UIConfig
extends java.lang.Object
    Template class to store values of Joystick button IDs and ports so that buttons can be sorted by function regardless of which physical device they're on.
    Author:
    Nick

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      CarbonUI.UIConfig()
      All control elements are constructed with an 'UNINITIALIZED' port and ID, that way if a particular control is not defined for a specific controller, the program can catch that at execution.

    • Constructor Detail

      • CarbonUI.UIConfig

        public CarbonUI.UIConfig()
        All control elements are constructed with an 'UNINITIALIZED' port and ID, that way if a particular control is not defined for a specific controller, the program can catch that at execution.

    • Method Detail

      • setDefaultUI

        public void setDefaultUI()
        Loads the values specified by the constants in UIConfig into the UIElement objects. The UIElement objects hold the values which are actively referenced for control information, so setting these to match the default values in effect resets the controls to the default.
